      "status": "confirmed",
      "title": "(C) Feds at Aster",
      "location": "",
      "description": "LOAD IN: 6:30pm Sun-Thu | 7pm Fri-Sat<br>SOUNDCHECK: 7pm Sun-Thu | 7:30pm Fri-Sat<br>SET TIMES: 8pm-10pm Sun-Thu | 8:30pm-10:30pm Fri-Sat<br>SET LENGTH: Time slot is 2 hours. Serving staff appreciates an intermission (10-20min) to deliver food and take final orders for the night. Prior to showtime, please tell a Manager if you anticipate your show ending early.<br>CURFEW:  10:15pm Sun-Thu, 11:15pm Fri-Sat<br>STAGE SIZE: 13’ X 7’ or “snug”<br>TECH: We provide a full PA system with monitors, lights, microphones, cables etc. You will have the option to have your show recorded by your scheduled soundtech. If you opt-in for this paid added service, let us know as soon as possible so we can prepare accordingly. <br>Backline is not provided by venue. Please coordinate with any co-billed act for equipment sharing. <br>LOAD-IN: Pull up outside the Aster Cafe, on SE Main St. and throw on your flashers - but be prompt as parking enforcement is strict. You can arrive earlier than your check time to load in gear, but you may have to wait for the sound tech. There is no green room available, so all equipment cases should be moved to our storage room by 15 minutes to showtime - please consult the soundtech, or any Aster employee, for access. This keeps our small stage, walkways and doorways clear and reduces propping doors open as a courtesy to  staff and patrons dining.<br>SET TIME: Performance is to begin at the agreed set time. We reserve the right to cut off the performance should it extend beyond the agreed set times.<br>PARKING: Underground tunnel connected parking is available in the St. Anthony Falls ramp on 2nd St &amp; 2nd Ave. The meters in this area and on Main street are in effect until 12 Midnight (the meters on 2nd St. SE behind Aster Cafe are cheaper than on Main Street!) Aster is not to be held responsible for parking citations. <br>**Please Note: For safety reasons, performers can request an escort from an Aster staff member to their parked car.<br>PAYMENT: 75% of the cover, paid to W9 submitter/single payee after equipment tear down. In the event of a multiple act bill, the different acts will need to find a way to disperse payment.<br><br>WALK-INS: Our shared goal is for a full cafe space during live music filled with smiling faces vibing with your tunes. Sometimes a full cafe doesn't materialize, and in the interest of getting guests in seats, we will strike a deal at the door with walk-in guests to pay a single cover charge per group, rather than insist on a cover charge per person. We want to entice guests to stay for dinner service, and in \"striking a deal\" they're likely to stay, the musicians have a fuller room, and still retains a cover. Walk-in guests approaching the host stand \"for the music\" are charged one cover charge per adult, but for walk-ins that are coming just for dinner, having a collaborative option available allows greater guest retention.<br>HOSPITALITY: Please inquire with bar staff to be issued your two complimentary drink tickets for each person who goes on stage. N/A Beverages available. **Please Note: The kitchen closes at 9pm Sun-Thurs and 10pm Fri-Sat and food orders must be placed before this time, no exceptions<br>MERCH: Inquire with Aster staff about setting up a merch table. Typically a table is available near the entrance or, alternatively, a table near the stage.<br>_______________<br>PROMOTIONS: Import the Facebook event into your Fan Page by clicking on the 3 dotted button, and selecting \"Add to Page\". Please use this to invite guests and in your general promotions  to funnel all traffic to one place. We encourage you to boost the event itself (not make an Ad), and Aster will reimburse you up to $20! Simply provide us with the boost results/receipt prior to your show. The success of your event relies heavily on your promotional efforts.<br>PROMO MATERIALS: We need a photo, bio, links to your content, desired ticket price, and completed W9 (so we can pay you!) prior to the agreed upon show date. These items allow us to promote your show with social media, multiple posters and a newsletter to our 45,000 subscribers! Please fill out our W9-Request Form prior to your show by following <a href=\"https://www.cognitoforms.com/LuckyClubEntertainment/W9RequestForm\">this link</a>.<br>GUEST LIST: If you have a guest list, please provide the Talent Buyer with names as early as possible as well as a written list for Aster staff when you arrive on the day of the show to ensure seating is accounted for.. <br>TECH: We provide a full PA system with monitors, lights, microphones, cables <br>_______________<br>PROFESSIONAL COURTESIES: Stage and house volume is under the control of Aster management at all times. A ceiling of 100 db maximum in the cafe will be observed, both from the house PA and from amplification on stage. If you exceed this limit, you will receive a warning and if you fail to comply, you will be shut down. Our first responsibility is to our guest—we ask you to please act accordingly.<br>Please, no “digital tip jars” or table flyers soliciting payment! This is a form of solicitation, and we don’t allow it at shows. Thanks!",
